.TH ME 1
.SH NAME
me \- show identity summary for the current user and environment
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B me
.RI [ flags ]
.br
.B me whoami
.br
.B me id
.RI [ GNU\ id\ options ]
.SH DESCRIPTION
The default
.B me
command prints identity information using structured providers.
.PP
By default (when
.B \-\-source
is not used), these providers run, in order:
.BR osaccount ,
.BR envcontext ,
.BR network ,
.BR sysinfo ,
and
.BR authproviders
(git and cloud identity hints).
If any
.B \-\-source
is given, it
.I replaces
that full default list entirely (list only the providers you want).
.PP
.B me whoami
prints the effective user name (GNU whoami compatibility).
.PP
.B me id
prints user and group identifiers (GNU id compatibility, documented subset of options).
.SH OPTIONS
See
.B me \-\-help
for the full flag list, including the complete
.B \-\-source
description and all valid provider names.
.SH EXIT STATUS
0 on success, 2 for usage errors, 3 for strict/provider failures, 4 for internal errors.
